      <pb n="1"/>
        <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>April 27&#44; 1854</date>.</p>
        <p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leaser</addressee></sic>&#44; Esq.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">By the present we beg to<lb/> hand you our card for the purpose to call your<lb/> attention to the fact that it would perhaps be of<lb/> some benefit to you to confide us your agency for the<lb/> sale of your books&#44; such as bibles &#38;c &#38;c.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As regards to our <del>ch</del> <sic>caracter</sic> &#38;c we beg to refer<lb/> you to <persName>Miss. Bernhimer Brother D</persName>&#44; with which<lb/> gentlemen our <persName role="author">Mr. Thalmessinger<add>&#63;</add></persName> has been as<lb/> Bookkeeper for the last 3 &#189; years.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Isaac Bernhimer</persName> being at your place at present<lb/> you may perhaps find an <sic>oportunity</sic> to speak to him<lb/> about this subject.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Hoping to receive your favor as soon as possibly we are&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours very Resps.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Thalmessinger<add>&#63;</add></persName> &#38; <persName role="author">Benedict</persName></p>
      <pb n="2"/>
        <p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leaser</addressee></sic>&#44; Esq.</p>
